  <div class="comment-content">

    <div class="edit-comment-hide">
      <div class="comment-body markdown-body markdown-format js-comment-body">
          <p>Thanks for the feedback Ludwig.<br>
The method is actually useful, specially for newcomers.</p>

<p>Its use is supposed to be outside strict directives, e.g. like in our <a href="https://github.com/mapsforge/mapsforge/blob/dev/docs/Getting-Started-Android-App.md">Getting-Started-Android-App</a> guide.</p>

<p>I had made a simple implementation in <a href="https://github.com/mapsforge/mapsforge/blob/dev/Applications/Android/Samples/src/main/java/org/mapsforge/applications/android/samples/SimplestMapViewer.java">SimplestMapViewer</a> where indeed we have to override the partial destroy methods just for the sake of it.</p>

<p>Or else we need to alter the base class (i.e. <code>MapViewerTemplate</code>) and its derivatives. I can look at it.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>
