  <div class="comment-content">

    <div class="edit-comment-hide">
      <div class="comment-body markdown-body email-format js-comment-body">
          <div class="email-fragment">I wonder if it should just be integrated into the MVT?
Am 04.08.2015 14:09 schrieb "Emux" &lt;notifications@github.com&gt;:</div>
<span class="email-hidden-toggle"><a href="#">…</a></span><div class="email-hidden-reply" style="display:none">
<div class="email-quoted-reply"> Thanks for the feedback Ludwig.
 The method is actually useful, specially for newcomers.

 Its use is supposed to be outside strict directives, e.g. like in our
 Getting-Started-Android-App
 &lt;<a href="https://github.com/mapsforge/mapsforge/blob/dev/docs/Getting-Started-Android-App.md">https://github.com/mapsforge/mapsforge/blob/dev/docs/Getting-Started-Android-App.md</a>&gt;
 guide.

 I had made a simple implementation in SimplestMapViewer
 &lt;<a href="https://github.com/mapsforge/mapsforge/blob/dev/Applications/Android/Samples/src/main/java/org/mapsforge/applications/android/samples/SimplestMapViewer.java">https://github.com/mapsforge/mapsforge/blob/dev/Applications/Android/Samples/src/main/java/org/mapsforge/applications/android/samples/SimplestMapViewer.java</a>&gt;
 where indeed we have to override some partial destroy methods just for the
 sake of it.

 Or else we need to alter the base class (i.e. MapViewerTemplate) and its
 derivatives. I can look at it.

 —
